            <idno type="URI">https://architecturasinica.org/keyword/k000249</idno>
            <note type="Note"><p xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000249-3">Tiaojindouke 挑金斗科, literally “propping gold bracket set” is one of the bracket set (douke斗科) types used in Ming and Qing dynasty official architecture and can be used as an intercolumnar (pingshenke 平身科), corner jiaoke角科, and/or pillar top bracket set (zhutouke柱头科).The word tiao 挑 means to prop up (Kroll), and jin 金 in this case refers to the lowest interior purlin (xiajinheng下金桁). According to the Qing court manual Gongcheng Zuofa《工程做法》, tiaojin douke is a bracket set that connects the eaves purlin (yanheng 檐桁) to the interior purlin (jinheng金桁) via one or more slanted timber bars (chenggan 秤杆)  (Gongbu 1734, 28.16b).  The slanted timber bar echoes the form of the Song dynasty xia’ang 下昂 (k000178), but it functions less for roof load transfer and more as a stabilizing component locking the eaves to the interior structure. The structure is similar to that of the liujindouke 溜金斗科, but it differs in the following two ways: 1) the rear end of the chenggan supports the huatai bracket set (huataike 花台科) instead of being supported by it; 2) instead of being supported by a squared beam (huataifang 花台枋), the huatai bracket set and the slanted timber bar are connected from the bottom by a wooden peg called fulianshao 伏蓮捎. Modern scholars refer to the tiaojintouke 挑金斗科 and the liujindouke 溜金斗科 collectively as the liujindougong 溜金斗栱 (Liang Sicheng, 1981, 108).</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000249-3">	挑金斗科，是明清官式建築中的一種斗栱類型，可用作平身科、柱头科、角科（工部1734，28·16b）。“挑”有揚起、舉起的意思（数字版漢語大辭典），“金”指金桁。根據清工部《工程做法》（工部1734，29·32a），挑金斗科指以斜向構件聯系簷桁和金桁的斗栱。秤桿在形式上類似於宋式斗栱中的昂，但其主要作用是將簷口與內部屋架結構穩固的連接，而不是傳遞屋面荷載。挑金斗科做法與溜金斗科相似，但有以下兩點區別：（1）秤桿後尾支撐花臺科，而不是被花臺科承托；（2）秤桿後尾與花臺科由伏蓮捎連接固定，而不是由花臺枋承托。現代學者多將挑金斗栱和溜金斗栱統稱為溜金斗栱（梁1981，108）。</p>
